javadoc:
Command for changing the scope of a label.
 The scope is the namespace that the label is associated with.

methods.name: <init>
methods.comment: Constructs a new command for changing the scope of a label.

params.name: addr
params.comment: the address of the label to be changed.

params.name: name
params.comment: the name of the label to be changed.

params.name: oldNamespace
params.comment: the current scope of the label that will be changed.

params.name: newNamespace
params.comment: the new scope of the label.
